    {
      "id": "PopularPost210643",
      "post_content": "The good Arcbound critters: This guy, [Arcbound Worker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Worker), [Arcbound Slith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Slith), [Arcbound Stinger](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Stinger), [Arcbound Fiend](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Fiend) and maybe [Arcbound Reclaimer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Reclaimer).  \n  \nStill, building a decent deck around them is not easy. [Energy Chamber](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Energy Chamber)s, proliferate, mana accel stuff ([Sphere of Suns](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sphere of Suns) and [Everflowing Chalice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Everflowing Chalice) come to mind) can build a dcent support system, but the biggest problem is they're too vulnerable while you amass an army of them.",
      "posted_by": "djflo",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost210643\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">The good Arcbound critters: This guy, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Worker\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Worker\">Arcbound Worker</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Slith\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Slith\">Arcbound Slith</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Stinger\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Stinger\">Arcbound Stinger</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Fiend\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Fiend\">Arcbound Fiend</a> and maybe <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Reclaimer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Reclaimer\">Arcbound Reclaimer</a>.<br/><br/>Still, building a decent deck around them is not easy. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Energy Chamber\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Energy Chamber\">Energy Chamber</a>s, proliferate, mana accel stuff (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sphere of Suns\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sphere of Suns\">Sphere of Suns</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Everflowing Chalice\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Everflowing Chalice\">Everflowing Chalice</a> come to mind) can build a dcent support system, but the biggest problem is they're too vulnerable while you amass an army of them.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '210643'); return false;\">\r\n 